pageContext.claim: “We've done, I think, on average, really phenomenally as a country. I think we've done phenomenally.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump made this comment when the number of deaths in the United States was nearly 6,000. A little more than a week later, the death toll topped 20,000, the highest of any country in the world. Looking at the numbers on a per capita basis -- the death toll per million people -- the United States is in the top ten of major countries.
